76
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:39,260
to my great father.

77
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,100
To our great

78
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:41,620
Mr. Li Dafu.

79
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,900
Come on, Mr. Li Dafu.

80
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:43,930
- Let's toast to you.
- Together now.

81
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:44,380
Together.

82
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:45,420
Coach, thank you.

83
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,420
Thank you, Coach.

84
00:04:46,420 --> 00:04:47,640
- Thank you, Coach.
- Thank you, Coach.

85
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:58,000
She's my daughter.

86
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,160
The pit was dug by me.

87
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:02,920
Luckily, I didn't bury myself.

88
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,200
Right, right.

89
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:09,180
Now that we've got the prize money,

90
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:10,360
what are your plans?

91
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:13,360
Spend the prize money and live it up a bit.

92
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,960
What about you, Mascot?

93
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:17,320
Me?

94
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:19,060
I'll probably save my prize money

95
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,080
for future needs.

96
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:21,720
Future needs?

97
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,020
Saving up for a wife, huh?

98
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:26,100
What are you talking about?

99
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,700
I'm just being prepared for the future.

100
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,140
What do you know? Come on, drink up.

101
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,440
- Come on.
- What about you, Weilan?

102
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:32,880
Well.

103
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,980
Growing up,

104
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:37,360
I've always won trophies,

105
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,870
but this is the first time winning prize money.

106
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:41,460
I'll give the prize money to my grandpa

107
00:05:41,460 --> 00:05:42,300
to make him happy.

108
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,160
Grandpa?

109
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:45,720
You're so filial.

110
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,520
I want to go on a trip.

111
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:51,080
Duoduo, what about you?

112
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,960
Me?

113
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,580
Well, I have big plans for it.

114
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,600
What big plans?

115
00:05:58,740 --> 00:05:59,560
That's a secret.

116
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,160
Come on.

117
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:07,020
Let's toast again to victory!

118
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:08,220
- Alright, alright.
- Alright, come on.

119
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,620
- Another toast.
- Thanks, Coach.

120
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,920
Cheers!

121
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,040
It's getting late.

122
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:22,040
You guys go on with your secrets.

123
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:24,580
I'm taking my peanuts

124
00:06:24,580 --> 00:06:25,980
and drinks elsewhere.

125
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:26,480
Coach,

126
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:27,820
- drink with us!
- Come on.

127
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:28,700
Yes, eat with us.

128
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:29,710
- You guys go ahead.
- Drink with us.

129
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:31,760
- Uncle, drink with us here!
- You guys have fun.

130
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,300
Here, have some shredded potatoes and edamame.

131
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,600
- Fill it up.
- What are you doing?

132
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:35,800
Can't you see?

133
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:37,320
What?

134
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:38,900
Keep him company.

135
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:39,600
Go.

136
00:06:42,460 --> 00:06:44,120
Come on. Let's drink.

137
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:45,880
Keep it up!

138
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:47,940
- Keep it up!
- Keep it up!

139
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:48,920
Cheers!

140
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:58,500
(Dafu BBQ)

141
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,260
Mom, I'm coming down.

142
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:03,320
We're coming down, Auntie.

143
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,500
How's the food? Is it enough?

144
00:07:05,780 --> 00:07:06,900
- The kebabs smell great.
- Eat more.

145
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:08,200
- You ate too little.
- How about the drinks?

146
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:08,900
Respect.

147
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:09,580
- Fine.
- Mom.

148
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:10,300
Let's keep going.

149
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,340
Your husband can really drink.

150
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,460
Shao Nian can't keep up at all.

151
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:13,900
He's going on and on.

152
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:16,220
Alright, stop teasing me.

153
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:17,860
Go to Aunt Zhou's place
and get me two dragon fruits.

154
00:07:17,860 --> 00:07:19,540
- I'm running low.
- I'll go get them.

155
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:20,260
- Okay.
- Thank you.

156
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,700
Mom, you're the best.

157
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:26,180
Always so thoughtful.

158
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,580
Now you think of me.

159
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:30,980
I saw you toasting your coach

160
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:32,180
non-stop earlier.

161
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:33,500
Why?

162
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,100
Are you jealous?

163
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,420
I'm not jealous at all.

164
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:39,140
I'm your logistics chief.

165
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:41,380
I deserve half of the credit.

166
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:43,060
Of course, all the credit goes to you.

167
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:43,940
Come on.

168
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:45,140
You're my beautiful, charming,

169
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:46,380
and kind-hearted mom.

170
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:47,100
Love you.

171
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,380
Alright. Don't disturb me.

172
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,860
I'm getting goosebumps here. Go over there.

173
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:53,340
Let me do it. Go be with your husband.

174
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,740
If he gets drunk, no one can handle him.

175
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:56,140
- Let me handle it.
- Alright.

176
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:57,180
I'll go take care of him.

177
00:07:57,980 --> 00:07:59,460
Thinking about the match

178
00:07:59,460 --> 00:08:00,780
makes my hands shake.

179
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:04,460
Drinking well, huh, Gao?

180
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,380
Of course.

181
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:06,540
Where's Auntie?

182
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,100
She went upstairs to be with my dad.

183
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:08,740
Thank you.

184
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:11,140
Be careful not to cut yourself.

185
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:14,420
Take it. It's for you.

186
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:16,420
What's this?

187
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:19,220
You lent me 10,000 yuan tuition fee, remember?

188
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:19,660
Hurry, take it.

189
00:08:20,780 --> 00:08:21,940
I didn't even play in the game.

190
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:22,820
The prize money is enough.

191
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:24,060
We're even now.

192
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:25,260
- You should keep it.
- You have to take it.

193
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,060
This is different.

194
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:26,980
It's not the same.

195
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:28,500
You have to take it. Don't look back.

196
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,450
Take it before the others see.

197
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,300
Come on, take it.

198
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:32,020
Then I'll take it.

199
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,260
Let me know if you need money again.

200
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:34,620
Okay, got it.

201
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:35,660
Be careful not to cut yourself.

202
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:36,940
Go back and join them.

203
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,540
What are you talking about?

204
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:39,340
Give me my cup.

205
00:08:40,380 --> 00:08:41,660
The fruit will be ready soon.

206
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:46,460
Where's Shao Nian?

207
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,100
In the kitchen, washing dishes.

208
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:52,140
Let me handle this. You should head back.

209
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:53,420
Don't stay too late.

210
00:08:53,420 --> 00:08:54,820
I'll help you clean up.

211
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:00,380
Your spikes were weak during the game.

212
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:02,260
Is your old wrist injury

213
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:03,300
acting up again?

214
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:04,180
No.

215
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,900
Then why were your spikes so weak?

216
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:09,260
I just didn't play at my normal level.

217
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,980
That's definitely not your usual level.

218
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:14,460
Is your wrist really okay?

219
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,220
It's fine.

220
00:09:16,820 --> 00:09:17,860
Don't worry about me.

221
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:19,700
Leave these. I'll help you clean up later.

222
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:32,620
(Xingang University)

223
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:18,180
Go.

224
00:10:56,860 --> 00:10:57,580
What's wrong?

225
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,180
Are you okay?

226
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:00,500
I'm tired.

227
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:01,900
I'll rest for a bit.

228
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:10,820
I'll go check.

229
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:17,540
Come in.

230
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:21,620
Chen Weilan,

231
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:23,620
there's still an issue with your spiking.

232
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:26,060
Are you worried about your wrist injury?

233
00:11:26,460 --> 00:11:27,220
Actually,

234
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:28,420
beach volleyball isn't as likely

235
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:29,720
to cause injuries as indoor volleyball.

236
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,300
If you're really worried,

237
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,940
you could wear a wrist guard.
Wouldn't that help?

238
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:36,300
Why should I wear a wrist guard? No need.

239
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,780
I just care about you.

240
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:41,460
Thank you.

241
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:46,820
Weilan,

242
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:48,420
isn't this your wrist guard?

243
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:49,660
Why aren't you wearing it?

244
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,900
(Yang Liyun)

245
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:45,220
It's been a while
since we played volleyball together.

246
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,100
Yes.

247
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,020
It's rare.

248
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:47,860
Let's hang out tonight.

249
00:12:47,860 --> 00:12:48,740
- Yang Liyun.
- Let's hang out.

250
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,220
I need to talk to you.

251
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:53,740
You all go ahead.

252
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:54,540
Bye-bye.

253
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:03,140
What's the matter?

254
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:04,420
Take a look at this video.

255
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:06,180
Is this you?

256
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:07,380
You were wearing a wrist guard.

257
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:09,660
Yes.

258
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:11,060
It looks similar

259
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:12,500
to mine,

260
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:13,780
but

261
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,340
what does that prove?

262
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,020
That day, I was rushing out with Liang,

263
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:24,380
and I accidentally saw you
wearing that wrist guard

264
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:25,500
and recording.

265
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,860
You can't deny it.

266
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:28,980
You were right behind me,

267
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:31,100
so the angle of the video online

268
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,780
matches mine.

269
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,940
Did you know Gao Ge was suspended

270
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:38,500
for six months because of this video?

271
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:40,780
So, please come back

272
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:41,900
to our school with me

273
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:43,540
and explain everything to the school leaders.

274
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:44,340
Alright?

275
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:46,300
Chen Weilan,

276
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,580
when did you become a busybody?

277
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:49,900
So nosy.

278
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:52,380
I'm not being nosy.

279
00:13:52,820 --> 00:13:54,140
Gao Ge thinks

280
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:55,740
I posted the video.

281
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,260
He's misunderstanding me.

282
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,620
I'm taking the fall for you.

283
00:13:59,620 --> 00:14:01,140
Don't you think you owe me an explanation?

284
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,420
I'm not going.

