00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:04,620
He was fighting. It's a fact.

286
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:05,780
What's there to explain?

287
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,980
Then why did you do it?

288
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,020
Because I like him.

289
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:16,860
But he only

290
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,700
has Lang Yueting in his heart.

291
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,380
He wouldn't even say a word to me.

292
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,340
And now,

293
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:23,860
he's known as a rogue who fights.

294
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:25,980
Lang Yueting will never look at him now.

295
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:27,540
Even if he didn't fight,

296
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:29,820
I wouldn't like him.

297
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:33,500
Yueting, it wasn't intentional.

298
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:34,860
Listen to me.

299
00:14:34,860 --> 00:14:36,220
Really, I just...

300
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:37,780
You did nothing wrong. No need to apologize.

301
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,500
Who's suspended or taking the blame

302
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:40,540
doesn't concern me.

303
00:14:40,540 --> 00:14:42,340
These are all trivial matters.

304
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:43,460
- Let's go.
- Lang Yueting.

305
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:50,220
Do you really not care

306
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:51,900
that I've been suspended?

307
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:53,700
Right?

308
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:56,300
Right.

309
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:58,980
What do you have to do with me?

310
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:01,540
Why would your suspension matter to me?

311
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:02,500
Besides,

312
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,100
you're suspended because you fought.

313
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,940
You did it. You can't blame anyone else.

314
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:09,180
Lang Yueting,

315
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:11,580
you're an athlete.

316
00:15:11,580 --> 00:15:13,260
You know that a suspension

317
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:14,740
is a blemish on an athlete's record.

318
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,140
How can you say that?

319
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:22,260
Now I understand.

320
00:15:22,660 --> 00:15:24,780
You won that MVP award...

321
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:26,060
Impressive.

322
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:29,780
Are you just upset

323
00:15:29,780 --> 00:15:31,420
about the last Youth National Team selection?

324
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:32,740
Can't accept that?

325
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:34,020
We can have another match.

326
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,020
- Sure.
- Enough.

327
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:38,660
Chen Weilan.

328
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:40,740
Thank you.

329
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:45,500
Come on.

330
00:15:50,980 --> 00:15:52,900
You'll come with me to my school.

331
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:54,900
Gao Ge, why did you run away?

332
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:57,060
Ignore them.

333
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,300
Gao Ge, why did you run away?

334
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:04,620
I've found the recorder.

335
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:05,980
Explain it to the school,

336
00:16:05,980 --> 00:16:07,540
so you won't be suspended.

337
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:13,620
So, as I said,

338
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:16,220
thank you.

339
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:18,900
That's your attitude?

340
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:20,020
What do you want?

341
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:22,580
What do I want?

342
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:23,780
Dude, this is your problem.

343
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,700
I cleaned up your mess.

344
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,620
Don't bother me again.

345
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,420
And what about my wrist guard?

346
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,420
Consider us even.

347
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:40,740
You've wronged me for so long,

348
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:42,020
and you just want to call it even?

349
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:48,020
Fine.

350
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,180
I'm sorry.

351
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:57,420
You get all soft when you see Lang Yueting.

352
00:16:57,420 --> 00:16:58,380
And you?

353
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:06,180
Did I get soft just now for your sake?

354
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:01,940
Are you alright?

355
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:03,420
Are you okay, Weilan?

356
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:08,900
My hand hurts a bit. I'll rest for a while.

357
00:18:10,780 --> 00:18:12,700
Your old injury acts up around certain people.

358
00:18:13,140 --> 00:18:14,100
You were fine

359
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,260
when playing against Xia,

360
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,260
but you seemed hesitant

361
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:17,420
when Gao blocked.

362
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,300
Maybe Shao Nian should take another look at it.

363
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:21,220
Let me take a look.

364
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:23,220
It's not an old injury.

365
00:18:23,580 --> 00:18:24,340
It's a mental issue.

366
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,340
You're the one with a mental issue.

367
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:30,620
Enough for me. You guys continue.

368
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,020
A mental issue?

369
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:48,940
Wrist recovery period.

370
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:51,700
(Rehabilitation Training)
Conditions for recurrence after recovery.

371
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:53,940
Is there...

372
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:03,980
Wow, Duoduo.

373
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:05,260
It's been a semester,

374
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:06,540
and you're finally doing your homework?

375
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:08,380
You're just in time.

376
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:09,220
Let me ask you.

377
00:19:09,980 --> 00:19:11,980
After a wrist dislocation
has healed for a year,

378
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:13,220
under what circumstances

379
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:14,700
could it dislocate again?

380
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:16,620
And she exhibits different symptoms

381
00:19:16,620 --> 00:19:17,980
around different people.

382
00:19:17,980 --> 00:19:19,300
Sometimes she's fine,

383
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,220
and sometimes it suddenly acts up.

384
00:19:22,260 --> 00:19:23,340
You're asking all this

385
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:24,420
just to find out what happened

386
00:19:24,420 --> 00:19:26,260
to Chen Weilan's wrist

387
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:27,660
during the game with you and Gao, right?

388
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:28,380
Yes, yes.

389
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:30,860
Let me put it this way.

390
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,060
From a medical standpoint,

391
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,860
habitual dislocation is tough to cure,

392
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:37,500
and we can't rule out

393
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,700
psychological causes.

394
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:41,140
If there is

395
00:19:41,140 --> 00:19:42,140
no physical cause

396
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:43,500
like a heavy impact

397
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:45,100
or repetitive strain,

398
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:46,540
it is very likely

399
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:47,860
post-traumatic stress disorder

400
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:49,860
or some other psychological factor.

401
00:19:50,740 --> 00:19:52,700
Honestly,

402
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,740
I don't think there's anything wrong

403
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:55,820
with Chen Weilan's wrist.

404
00:19:56,340 --> 00:19:57,580
Look at this.

405
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:02,300
Look.

406
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:06,060
During your training,

407
00:20:06,060 --> 00:20:07,420
I secretly

408
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,140
recorded this game.

409
00:20:08,660 --> 00:20:09,780
Look at it.

410
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:11,340
The ball is coming.

411
00:20:11,860 --> 00:20:13,100
Look at her wrist.

412
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:14,660
It's strong, right?

413
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:16,460
And that spike was beautiful, wasn't it?

414
00:20:17,140 --> 00:20:18,060
But look.

415
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:19,220
This is yesterday's game.

416
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:20,900
Look at you and Gao.

417
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:21,900
Look at Chen Weilan's wrist.

418
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:23,900
When Gao blocks,

419
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,100
it suddenly

420
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,340
becomes weak, right?

421
00:20:26,820 --> 00:20:28,140
- Right?
- Yes. It's true.

422
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,020
That's a symptom

423
00:20:29,020 --> 00:20:30,580
of a psychosomatic injury.

424
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:32,820
So,

425
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,500
I think her wrist

426
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,620
is fully healed.

427
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,380
It's mostly psychological.

428
00:20:42,380 --> 00:20:43,460
Let's not dwell on that now.

429
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:45,300
Let me show you

430
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,660
