00:23:36,780 --> 00:23:38,660
You're just clumsy. Let me do it.

516
00:23:38,660 --> 00:23:39,500
No, I'll do it.

517
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:40,740
One of us hitting the hand is enough.

518
00:23:42,540 --> 00:23:43,540
- It's done.
- Great.

519
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:45,060
Here.

520
00:23:47,980 --> 00:23:48,460
Good.

521
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:52,100
- Looks nice.
- Looks nice.

522
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:54,380
Why are you copying me?

523
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:58,180
- Serve up!
- One, two, three, go!

524
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,420
Great, Jingxuan.

525
00:24:00,820 --> 00:24:02,140
Watch your angle on those spikes.

526
00:24:02,140 --> 00:24:02,860
Okay.

527
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:04,260
One, two, three, go!

528
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:06,260
Great shot!

529
00:24:07,340 --> 00:24:08,780
Weilan's spikes are really strong.

530
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:09,980
- One, two, three, go!
- Nice one.

531
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:10,860
Thank you, Coach.

532
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:12,340
Duoduo.

533
00:24:12,660 --> 00:24:13,820
What's wrong with you?

534
00:24:14,980 --> 00:24:16,140
Didn't I tell you about this?

535
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:17,060
Your elbow needs to be

536
00:24:17,380 --> 00:24:18,940
above your shoulder when spiking.

537
00:24:18,940 --> 00:24:20,740
- Have you forgotten about it?
- I had it up just now.

538
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:21,660
Didn't you see?

539
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:22,340
Alright.

540
00:24:22,820 --> 00:24:23,860
Let me show you again.

541
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:25,100
Watch carefully.

542
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:30,540
Bend your knees, squat down, feet apart.

543
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:33,860
Quickly push off the ground.

544
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:35,420
Lean forward.

545
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,700
When jumping,

546
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,940
put your elbow above your shoulder,

547
00:24:42,860 --> 00:24:45,100
your hand naturally beside your eye.

548
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:45,700
Alright.

549
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:47,460
Ready.

550
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:48,220
Jump!

551
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:53,300
- Coach!
- Uncle!

552
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,420
- Uncle Li!
- Coach, are you okay?

553
00:24:54,420 --> 00:24:55,540
Don't move. What's wrong with your leg?

554
00:24:55,540 --> 00:24:56,940
Wen Xin, get the doctor!

555
00:24:57,460 --> 00:24:58,420
Where does it hurt, Dad?

556
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:00,060
- Are you alright?
- Dad!

557
00:25:00,060 --> 00:25:01,620
- Take it easy.
- Dad, are you okay?

558
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:02,580
Dad!

559
00:25:03,020 --> 00:25:03,820
Are you okay?

560
00:25:04,060 --> 00:25:05,100
- Don't move.
- Don't move.

561
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,000
Does it hurt now?

562
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,020
We're from Xingang University's

563
00:25:07,020 --> 00:25:07,900
beach volleyball club.

564
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:09,140
Someone's injured.

565
00:25:09,140 --> 00:25:10,700
Can you send an ambulance?

566
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:11,660
What should we do?

567
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:16,300
(Outpatient)

568
00:25:17,220 --> 00:25:19,140
You're really overestimating yourself,

569
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,300
thinking you're still

570
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:21,660
a twenty-something.

571
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:22,980
You should be careful

572
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:24,500
doing demonstrations for Duoduo,

573
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:27,100
or you wouldn't have ended up in the hospital.

574
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:29,900
This has nothing to do with the demonstration.

575
00:25:32,620 --> 00:25:34,380
Glad you know it.

576
00:25:34,380 --> 00:25:36,700
You drank with Zheng
from next door, didn't you?

577
00:25:37,460 --> 00:25:38,340
It's fine.

578
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:40,380
But you shouldn't have eaten seafood.

579
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:41,460
Now, your gout flared up, right?

580
00:25:41,460 --> 00:25:43,540
I was just celebrating a win.

581
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:44,860
You were happy, sure.

582
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:46,660
But I won't feed you now.

583
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:48,820
Drink a beer,

584
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:50,660
and suffer gout for days. Don't you know that?

585
00:25:51,260 --> 00:25:52,260
Now it's just me

586
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:53,460
and Shao Nian at the store.

587
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:55,460
I still have to take care of you,

588
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:57,180
which I don't mind,

589
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:58,820
but it's bad for business.

590
00:25:58,820 --> 00:26:00,460
And that means losing money.

591
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:01,780
We're already short on cash,

592
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:03,060
and now you're in the hospital,

593
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:04,540
costing us more.

594
00:26:04,540 --> 00:26:05,380
Money, money.

595
00:26:05,380 --> 00:26:06,420
All you think about is money.

596
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,540
Can money buy happiness?

597
00:26:09,180 --> 00:26:10,780
Can it replace family love?

598
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:12,620
Can it bring harmony with neighbors?

599
00:26:13,060 --> 00:26:14,420
So, as the old saying goes,

600
00:26:14,660 --> 00:26:15,940
just live each day well

601
00:26:16,460 --> 00:26:18,100
and live in the moment, okay?

602
00:26:18,340 --> 00:26:20,540
How can we live in the moment without money?

603
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:22,540
How can we be happy without money?

604
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:24,180
How can we find happiness without money?

605
00:26:24,180 --> 00:26:25,240
- I just don't understand.
- You...

606
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,900
We're talking about two different things here.

607
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:29,300
- Duoduo, what are you doing here?
- You don't understand what I'm saying at all.

608
00:26:29,300 --> 00:26:30,100
Why aren't you coming in?

609
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:32,420
Auntie, I brought some fruit for you.

610
00:26:32,420 --> 00:26:34,020
You can wash these and share them with Uncle.

611
00:26:34,340 --> 00:26:36,100
I'll take Duoduo out for a walk.

612
00:26:36,340 --> 00:26:37,460
- Okay, go ahead.
- I'll go now.

613
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,740
When did Duoduo arrive?

614
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,100
I'm not sure.

615
00:26:50,740 --> 00:26:51,500
What's wrong?

616
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:52,980
You seem upset.

617
00:26:57,060 --> 00:26:58,580
It's just a bit frustrating.

618
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:01,140
Your parents

619
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,420
have a good relationship.

620
00:27:02,660 --> 00:27:03,940
They just bicker sometimes.

621
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:04,900
It's normal.

622
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:07,020
Look.

623
00:27:07,740 --> 00:27:09,780
I asked my dad to join the team

624
00:27:10,180 --> 00:27:11,860
to coach us.

625
00:27:12,460 --> 00:27:14,580
But he ended up in the hospital

626
00:27:15,340 --> 00:27:16,820
so soon.

627
00:27:17,580 --> 00:27:18,460
Now the team

628
00:27:18,460 --> 00:27:19,740
can't train properly,

629
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:20,700
and everything's on hold.

630
00:27:21,060 --> 00:27:22,140
My mom is struggling

631
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:23,300
to manage the BBQ restaurant alone.

632
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:24,460
She can't handle it on her own.

633
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:26,500
And Chen Weilan...

634
00:27:26,980 --> 00:27:29,100
She has so many issues,

635
00:27:29,100 --> 00:27:31,260
but we don't even know what they are.

636
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:32,660
All in all, there are so many problems.

637
00:27:33,180 --> 00:27:34,940
I was hoping my dad could help her,

638
00:27:35,260 --> 00:27:36,060
but now

639
00:27:37,980 --> 00:27:40,060
everything's a mess.

640
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:41,300
Don't worry too much.

641
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:42,780
I'm helping out

642
00:27:42,780 --> 00:27:43,940
at the BBQ restaurant.

643
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,660
I spoke to the doctor earlier,

644
00:27:45,660 --> 00:27:47,140
and they said Uncle Li's condition

645
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,460
is just a mild gout attack.

646
00:27:48,860 --> 00:27:50,780
As long as he rests well in the hospital

647
00:27:50,780 --> 00:27:52,620
and controls his diet,

648
00:27:52,620 --> 00:27:53,820
he should be fine.

649
00:27:55,460 --> 00:27:57,300
As for the beach volleyball coach,

650
00:27:57,980 --> 00:27:59,340
we can figure something out.

651
00:27:59,340 --> 00:28:00,620
I'm sure we'll find a solution.

652
00:28:58,820 --> 00:28:59,540
Dad.

653
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:01,500
Duoduo.

654
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,900
- You should've slept longer.
- You're here.

655
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:08,380
I'm fine.

656
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:09,380
Go home

657
00:29:09,900 --> 00:29:11,580
and help your mom with the work.

658
00:29:13,780 --> 00:29:14,860
Even while sick,

659
00:29:14,860 --> 00:29:16,540
you're still thinking about your store.

660
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:20,540
Without the store,

661
00:29:21,140 --> 00:29:22,780
how will you pay for college?

662
00:29:22,780 --> 00:29:25,540
You'd only play beach volleyball
in your dreams.

663
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:28,220
Take care of your health first.

664
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:30,500
Drink less alcohol in the future.

665
00:29:32,220 --> 00:29:32,900
Alright.

666
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:34,980
I know.

667
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:38,460
Just focus

668
00:29:39,740 --> 00:29:41,460
on practicing your volleyball.

669
00:29:42,460 --> 00:29:43,420
You've improved

670
00:29:44,100 --> 00:29:45,740
your quick spikes,

671
00:29:45,740 --> 00:29:46,780
but you still need to work

672
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:49,020
on your form for spiking.

673
00:29:51,510 --> 00:29:52,460
And

674
00:29:52,650 --> 00:29:53,620
I think

675
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:55,660
Chen Weilan

676
00:29:55,660 --> 00:29:57,460
is a rare talent.

677
00:29:57,460 --> 00:29:59,560
Don't drive her away.

678
00:30:00,420 --> 00:30:01,380
Alright, alright.

679
00:30:01,860 --> 00:30:03,460
Even when you're sick,

680
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:05,140
you still can't say something nice.

681
00:30:06,820 --> 00:30:09,020
If you really want to train us well,

682
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:10,820
get better soon.

683
00:30:11,500 --> 00:30:13,260
Take care of yourself.

684
00:30:13,260 --> 00:30:13,940
Okay?

685
00:30:16,660 --> 00:30:17,220
Okay.

686
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:19,020
I'll get better soon.

687
00:30:19,900 --> 00:30:20,860
Once I'm out of here,

688
00:30:21,260 --> 00:30:23,540
I'll train you all properly.

689
00:30:24,020 --> 00:30:25,940
You're getting eager.

690
00:30:27,740 --> 00:30:28,820
Just rest up

691
00:30:28,820 --> 00:30:30,180
and recover first.

692
00:30:34,060 --> 00:30:35,300
Duoduo, stop practicing.

693
00:30:35,620 --> 00:30:36,820
Come and have some late-night noodles.

694
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:39,540
Here.

695
00:30:41,020 --> 00:30:42,580
Why is it instant noodles again?

696
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:45,020
I don't know how to cook anything else.

697
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:46,020
This is all I can make.

698
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:47,700
And you still have the nerve
to apply for a job at our place?

699
00:30:48,450 --> 00:30:51,040
♪Under the sun, the waves are shining♪

700
00:30:51,060 --> 00:30:52,220
I can't apply for anything else.

701
00:30:52,620 --> 00:30:53,660
I can't do anything else.

702
00:30:59,380 --> 00:31:00,380
Isn't that Lang Yueting?

703
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:01,380
Gao's goddess?

704
00:31:02,580 --> 00:31:03,620
Gao Ge's goddess?

705
00:31:03,620 --> 00:31:05,740
Yeah. He usually doesn't say much.

706
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:07,580
But he's really into her.

707
00:31:07,950 --> 00:31:10,070
♪Amazing like the stars♪

708
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:14,810
♪The shadow is like the sketch of a memory♪

709
00:31:16,020 --> 00:31:18,020
Chen Weilan is really odd.

710
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,100
She's usually great at volleyball

711
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:21,100
with you guys.

712
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:22,620
But did you see that ball just now?

713
00:31:23,300 --> 00:31:24,860
When Lang Yueting blocked,

714
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:26,500
Weilan's wrist seemed to lose power.

715
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:27,140
Look.

716
00:31:27,330 --> 00:31:29,480
♪Look at you messing around♪

717
00:31:30,220 --> 00:31:31,420
What do you mean?

718
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:32,700
Look at the ball just now.

719
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:33,900
Did you see how her wrist looked hurt

720
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:35,580
when Lang Yueting blocked just now?

721
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:36,820
It was the same

722
00:31:36,820 --> 00:31:38,180
as when Gao blocked that day.

723
00:31:38,670 --> 00:31:40,890
♪Staying with you, relying on you♪

724
00:31:41,380 --> 00:31:43,740
So, is her wrist hurt or not?

725
00:31:44,420 --> 00:31:46,660
If she's injured,
why did she tell me she wasn't?

726
00:31:47,780 --> 00:31:50,300
If she's not,

727
00:31:50,860 --> 00:31:52,220
why can't she spike the ball properly

728
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:53,460
in front of Gao Ge?

729
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:57,030
♪I like every second of you♪

730
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:02,020
- What's so urgent?
- Come on.

731
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:02,900
Duoduo,

732
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:04,260
I've completed my mission.

733
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:05,700
Hello.

734
00:32:05,980 --> 00:32:06,740
Sit down.

735
00:32:11,740 --> 00:32:12,420
You're looking for me?

736
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:16,140
I wanted to ask you.

737
00:32:16,740 --> 00:32:17,860
What's the deal with you

738
00:32:18,660 --> 00:32:19,780
and Lang Yueting?

739
00:32:24,780 --> 00:32:25,580
There's nothing going on

740
00:32:26,300 --> 00:32:27,220
between us.

741
00:32:28,660 --> 00:32:29,700
Why do you ask?

742
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,380
Yesterday,

743
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:32,620
I watched a video of a match

744
00:32:32,620 --> 00:32:34,380
between Chen Weilan and Lang Yueting.

745
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:36,940
Do you remember our game from a few days ago?

746
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:38,860
Chen Weilan's performance

747
00:32:38,860 --> 00:32:40,340
was the same

748
00:32:40,620 --> 00:32:41,620
when facing you

749
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:42,780
and Lang Yueting.

750
00:32:43,620 --> 00:32:44,860
She hesitated

751
00:32:44,860 --> 00:32:45,980
and couldn't spike smoothly.

752
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:47,340
This phenomenon

753
00:32:47,620 --> 00:32:50,220
has been happening frequently lately.

754
00:32:50,860 --> 00:32:52,140
So, I wanted to ask you.

755
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:53,540
What exactly

756
00:32:54,180 --> 00:32:55,580
is going on?

757
00:33:00,780 --> 00:33:01,580
Weilan,

758
00:33:01,940 --> 00:33:03,220
isn't this your wrist guard?

759
00:33:03,220 --> 00:33:04,620
Why aren't you wearing it?

760
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:10,900
A few days ago,

761
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:12,140
Duoduo found

762
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:13,460
a wristband that Chen Weilan left behind.

763
00:33:13,820 --> 00:33:16,020
It looks exactly like the one
I gave to Lang Yueting.

764
00:33:16,420 --> 00:33:18,460
Afterward, I explained it to her.

765
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:26,460
Now I understand.

766
00:33:27,100 --> 00:33:28,820
Chen Weilan's psychological issue

767
00:33:29,140 --> 00:33:30,580
must be related to Lang Yueting.

768
00:33:31,340 --> 00:33:32,660
She knows that Gao

769
00:33:32,660 --> 00:33:34,100
had a crush on Lang Yueting,

770
00:33:34,620 --> 00:33:36,300
so when she plays against you,

771
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:37,900
she subconsciously replaces your face

772
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:39,140
with Lang Yueting's,

773
00:33:39,140 --> 00:33:40,980
making her nervous and hesitant.

774
00:33:43,140 --> 00:33:44,620
I'm sure that's the problem.

775
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:47,860
But we can't

776
00:33:47,860 --> 00:33:49,340
let this continue.

777
00:33:49,340 --> 00:33:51,260
What can we do about it?

778
00:33:51,540 --> 00:33:52,460
What can we do?

779
00:33:53,540 --> 00:33:55,740
I think we need to help Chen Weilan see it.

780
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:57,900
She needs to know where her problem lies

781
00:33:57,900 --> 00:33:59,260
before we can assist her.

782
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:00,340
How can we help her

783
00:34:00,340 --> 00:34:01,740
face her own issues?

784
00:34:07,380 --> 00:34:10,300
(Honor Certificate: Champion)

785
00:34:32,620 --> 00:34:33,460
How are you?

786
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:34,580
Are you alright?

787
00:34:42,060 --> 00:34:42,940
Did you notice it?

788
00:34:43,580 --> 00:34:44,380
Today,

789
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:45,900
Jingxuan's movements

790
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:47,180
were very similar to Lang Yueting's.

791
00:34:47,960 --> 00:34:49,420
We actually did that on purpose.

792
00:34:53,260 --> 00:34:54,900
Jingxuan, look at this movement.

793
00:34:57,420 --> 00:34:58,340
Do you see it?

794
00:35:00,900 --> 00:35:02,230
I think

795
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:03,940
since you just joined us

796
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:04,980
and haven't developed

797
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:06,660
a distinct style yet,

798
00:35:06,660 --> 00:35:08,460
asking you to mimic Lang Yueting

799
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:09,620
might be our best choice.

800
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:11,540
How am I supposed to mimic her?

801
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:14,020
Watch more videos.

802
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:15,860
For any technical moves you don't know,

803
00:35:15,860 --> 00:35:16,940
I'll guide you.

804
00:35:17,580 --> 00:35:18,740
Thank you.

805
00:35:19,500 --> 00:35:21,700
But Gao Ge, you're amazing.

806
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,780
You even know

807
00:35:23,780 --> 00:35:24,820
indoor volleyball moves?

808
00:35:25,740 --> 00:35:26,620
He's not just familiar

809
00:35:26,620 --> 00:35:28,220
with indoor volleyball.

810
00:35:28,220 --> 00:35:29,820
He knows Lang Yueting well.

811
00:35:30,060 --> 00:35:30,900
Mascot,

812
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:32,020
you talk too much.

813
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:34,100
Don't listen to his nonsense.

814
00:35:34,100 --> 00:35:34,820
Watch closely.

815
00:35:39,620 --> 00:35:41,100
When you're facing an opponent

816
00:35:41,100 --> 00:35:42,820
with a similar build to Lang Yueting,

817
00:35:42,820 --> 00:35:44,380
you can't execute a perfect spike.

818
00:35:45,180 --> 00:35:47,380
It's not because the opponent is skilled.

819
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:49,300
It's because their stance

820
00:35:49,300 --> 00:35:50,700
throws you off balance.

821
00:35:51,820 --> 00:35:52,740
Duoduo is right.

822
00:35:53,020 --> 00:35:54,780
Just like when you faced Gao,

823
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:55,620
you couldn't complete

824
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:56,900
your spike properly.

825
00:35:57,380 --> 00:35:59,700
It's because Lang Yueting
brings you too much pressure.

826
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:01,500
This mental barrier has never been resolved.

827
00:36:01,980 --> 00:36:03,020
To put it bluntly,

828
00:36:03,660 --> 00:36:04,980
it's a mental issue.

829
00:36:06,620 --> 00:36:07,940
And Lang Yueting's skill level

830
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:09,260
is similar to yours.

831
00:36:09,260 --> 00:36:10,500
So why does this happen to you?

832
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:12,340
Are you done?

833
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:15,860
Do you all have to do this today?

834
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:18,860
What exactly are you trying to do?

835
00:36:21,740 --> 00:36:22,860
Are you done?

836
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:26,100
Weilan?

837
00:36:37,620 --> 00:36:38,500
Chen Weilan?

838
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:40,660
Weilan?

839
00:36:42,060 --> 00:36:42,820
Weilan?

840
00:36:44,940 --> 00:36:46,540
Where did she go?

841
00:36:46,820 --> 00:36:48,140
Where did she go?

842
00:36:58,300 --> 00:37:00,860
Answer your phone, Chen Weilan.

843
00:37:12,180 --> 00:37:14,780
(Wen Xin; Has Chen Weilan contacted you?)

844
00:37:25,820 --> 00:37:28,340
(Beach Volleyball Activity Room)

845
00:37:30,060 --> 00:37:31,500
Did she reply to your message?

846
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:32,500
Where did she go?

847
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:37,300
No idea.

848
00:37:41,820 --> 00:37:43,140
We still don't know where she is.

849
00:37:43,140 --> 00:37:43,980
Where could she be?

850
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:45,460
Where could she be?

851
00:37:46,180 --> 00:37:47,020
No idea.

852
00:37:47,900 --> 00:37:48,540
Duoduo, you're here.

853
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,220
Any news about Chen Weilan?

854
00:37:51,460 --> 00:37:52,780
No.

855
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:54,540
Did she return to the dorm last night?

856
00:37:54,540 --> 00:37:55,860
No.

857
00:37:55,860 --> 00:37:56,820
I didn't sleep all night.

858
00:37:56,820 --> 00:37:58,220
Almost called the police.

859
00:37:58,220 --> 00:37:59,100
It's not that serious.

860
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:00,180
Where could she be?

861
00:38:04,700 --> 00:38:06,700
Maybe we were a bit too harsh.

862
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:08,300
Her self-esteem is strong.

863
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:09,740
She probably couldn't handle it.

864
00:38:09,740 --> 00:38:11,420
But she has to face her current issues.

865
00:38:11,420 --> 00:38:12,900
We need to help her, right?

866
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:18,740
But we didn't help her at all.

867
00:38:20,980 --> 00:38:22,780
The problem

868
00:38:22,780 --> 00:38:24,460
lies with Chen Weilan herself.

869
00:38:27,340 --> 00:38:29,500
She's so used to winning

870
00:38:29,500 --> 00:38:31,420
that she can't accept the blow of failure,

871
00:38:31,900 --> 00:38:33,820
especially losing

872
00:38:33,820 --> 00:38:34,900
to Lang Yueting.

873
00:38:45,540 --> 00:38:46,140
Dad.

874
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:47,420
We came to see you.

875
00:38:47,860 --> 00:38:48,980
Uncle Li, we're here.

876
00:38:49,460 --> 00:38:50,140
Hello.

877
00:38:50,540 --> 00:38:51,740
We brought you some fruit.

878
00:38:52,140 --> 00:38:53,420
How have you been resting lately?

879
00:38:55,020 --> 00:38:55,920
Can you give me an apple?

880
00:38:55,930 --> 00:38:57,500
It looks like I'll be here for a while.

881
00:38:58,420 --> 00:38:59,900
You're finally here.

882
00:38:59,900 --> 00:39:01,260
I'm so bored.

883
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:02,100
If you're too bored,

884
00:39:02,100 --> 00:39:03,660
we'll come by more often to chat with you.

885
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:05,500
- I'll get some water.
- Okay.

886
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:07,460
Let me peel an apple for you

887
00:39:07,460 --> 00:39:08,540
as a treat.

888
00:39:11,700 --> 00:39:13,340
I played five games

889
00:39:13,340 --> 00:39:14,540
with Gao Ge today,

890
00:39:14,540 --> 00:39:16,220
and he blocked all five of my shots.

891
00:39:18,220 --> 00:39:18,820
By the way,

892
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:20,340
about Chen Weilan.

893
00:39:20,660 --> 00:39:21,580
He talked to me

894
00:39:21,580 --> 00:39:22,820
about her issues today.

895
00:39:23,220 --> 00:39:24,700
But his explanation isn't clear to me.

896
00:39:25,180 --> 00:39:26,100
He mentioned something

897
00:39:26,980 --> 00:39:28,300
about not being able to handle losing

898
00:39:28,300 --> 00:39:29,980
after always winning.

899
00:39:30,700 --> 00:39:32,940
What's wrong with Chen Weilan?

900
00:39:33,540 --> 00:39:34,300
Duoduo,

901
00:39:34,700 --> 00:39:37,540
Gao Ge has already made it clear.

902
00:39:38,100 --> 00:39:39,060
Has he?

903
00:39:40,900 --> 00:39:43,260
Chen Weilan's issue is psychological.

904
00:39:43,260 --> 00:39:44,780
She can't handle losing.

905
00:39:45,100 --> 00:39:47,180
She'll never get past this mental barrier.

906
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:48,260
Duoduo,

907
00:39:48,780 --> 00:39:50,460
you also have a similar problem.

908
00:39:50,460 --> 00:39:51,300
You know?

909
00:39:51,700 --> 00:39:53,180
You know when you spike,

910
00:39:53,180 --> 00:39:54,420
you lack power,

911
00:39:54,660 --> 00:39:55,420
right?

912
00:39:55,900 --> 00:39:58,100
But when you're not sure you'll make the shot,

913
00:39:58,340 --> 00:39:59,820
you still keep spiking.

914
00:39:59,820 --> 00:40:00,900
This kind of mindset

915
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:03,900
is also a psychological issue.

916
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:05,500
I'm telling you.

917
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:07,300
If you can't get past this,

918
00:40:07,660 --> 00:40:09,340
you'll never improve.

919
00:40:10,900 --> 00:40:12,220
Think about it.

920
00:40:13,180 --> 00:40:14,460
I'm worried for you.

921
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:18,380
Are you okay, Duoduo?

922
00:40:18,380 --> 00:40:19,780
- I'm fine.
- Let's get you patched up.

923
00:40:20,060 --> 00:40:21,100
Uncle Li, have some water.

924
00:40:21,420 --> 00:40:22,580
- Hurry.
- Let's go.

925
00:40:24,220 --> 00:40:25,140
This kid.

926
00:40:34,060 --> 00:40:35,380
Always so careless.

927
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:36,340
Hold on for a bit.

928
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:50,540
Does it still hurt?

929
00:40:52,820 --> 00:40:53,540
Thank you.

930
00:40:55,220 --> 00:40:56,620
This little injury is nothing.

931
00:40:57,260 --> 00:40:59,180
The emotional pain my dad causes

932
00:40:59,180 --> 00:41:00,340
is the real pain.

933
00:41:00,780 --> 00:41:02,300
I know what you're thinking,

934
00:41:02,300 --> 00:41:03,940
but Uncle Li didn't mean it that way.

935
00:41:04,260 --> 00:41:05,460
You're just here

936
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:07,100
as a messenger from my dad,

937
00:41:07,380 --> 00:41:08,660
trying to smooth things over.

938
00:41:09,700 --> 00:41:11,940
I'm like the beef patty in a hamburger,

939
00:41:11,940 --> 00:41:13,060
stuck in the middle.

940
00:41:13,780 --> 00:41:16,020
Think about it. What Uncle Li said today

941
00:41:16,620 --> 00:41:17,460
was to teach you

942
00:41:17,460 --> 00:41:18,780
that you have to learn to lose

943
00:41:18,780 --> 00:41:19,780
before you can win.

944
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:21,500
Think about it.

945
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:22,620
For example, Chen Weilan

946
00:41:22,860 --> 00:41:24,820
has been known as a prodigy
since she was young,

947
00:41:25,140 --> 00:41:26,900
especially good at spiking,

948
00:41:26,900 --> 00:41:28,660
always hitting the mark, never losing.

949
00:41:29,060 --> 00:41:30,740
But once she loses,

950
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:32,420
it creates a huge psychological burden

951
00:41:32,420 --> 00:41:33,540
and shadow.

952
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:35,420
I think the Lang Yueting issue

953
00:41:35,420 --> 00:41:36,980
is just a trigger.

954
00:41:37,380 --> 00:41:38,860
In competitive sports,

955
00:41:38,860 --> 00:41:40,220
it's impossible to only win and never lose.

956
00:41:40,660 --> 00:41:42,060
Even in things you're really good at,

957
00:41:42,060 --> 00:41:43,460
you'll meet your match eventually.

958
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:44,220
Right?

959
00:41:46,900 --> 00:41:47,780
That makes sense.

960
00:41:53,100 --> 00:41:54,220
Xiaojing,

961
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:56,500
do you know what address Chen Weilan put down

962
00:41:56,500 --> 00:41:58,180
when she joined the beach volleyball team?

963
